им способом ты его откроешь?</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>there’s a lock on his door, and how will you open it?</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_СОПам."/><biblScope>II 73</biblScope></bibl></example><example><quote>læqwæn in færæti mækʼuræj æ kʼuma rasasta</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>юноша обухом топора сломал замок</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q/></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Iræf"/><biblScope>130</biblScope></bibl></example></exampleGrp><etym xml:lang="ru">По-видимому, следует связывать с <ref type="xr" target="#entry_kʼ0ym"/> | %ikʼum%i ‘угол’. Для развития значения ср. <mentioned xml:lang="en"><lang/> <w>lock</w> <gloss><q>замок</q></gloss></mentioned> при <mentioned xml:lang="de"><lang/> <w>Loch</w> <gloss><q>скрытое место</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="de"><w/> <gloss><q>нора</q></gloss></mentioned>,  и пр.</etym><etym xml:lang="en">Apparently, it should be connected with <ref type="xr" target="#entry_kʼ0ym"/> | %ikʼum%i ‘corner’. For the development of the meaning cf. <mentioned xml:lang="en"><lang/> <w>lock</w> <gloss><q>lock</q></gloss></mentioned> in the presence of <mentioned xml:lang="de"><lang/> <w>Loch</w> <gloss><q>concealed place</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="de"><w/> <gloss><q>burrow</q></gloss></mentioned>,  etc.</etym></entry></body></text></TEI>